"""Autogenerated numerical-correctness test for the FlyDSL ``gemm1_a4w4`` port.

This test is built **from the reference harness** ``/FlyDSL/test.py``: it reuses
that harness's KIMI-K2.5 MXFP4 MoE input/weight construction, preshuffle layouts
and per-1x32 quantisation so the unit test drives the kernel with exactly the
data layout it sees in production.

Ground truth = the **HIP / aiter gemm1 kernel** of this same kernel family,
i.e. ``aiter.mxfp4_moe_gemm1_a4w4`` which is the C++ codegen wrapper around
``csrc/kernels/mxfp4_moe/gemm_a4w4/gemm1_a4w4.cuh`` -- the exact HIP source the
FlyDSL port mirrors.  The variant (BM / kUseNT / kInlineQuant) is selected by
``token (M)`` exactly as the KIMI tuned CSV
(``kimik2_5_mxfp4_tuned_fmoe.csv``) dispatches it:

    token (M)      block_m   kernelName1                  flags
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
    1   .. 128     16        ..._BM16_INLINEQUANT         kUseNT=T kInlineQuant=T
    256 .. 512     32        ..._BM32_NT                  kUseNT=T kInlineQuant=F
    1024.. 2048    32        ..._BM32_CACHED              kUseNT=F kInlineQuant=F
    4096.. 32768   128       ..._BM128                    kUseNT=F kInlineQuant=F

We isolate **gemm1 only** (not the whole fused MoE):

  1. Reuse test.py ``build_weights``/``build_inputs`` -> KIMI hidden/topk + the
     ``mxfp4_moe`` preshuffled w1/w1_scale.
  2. Run the production gemm1 *prologue* (aiter ``mxfp4_moe_sort`` ->
     ``mxfp4_moe_quant`` -> ``mxfp4_moe_sort_scales``) at the variant's MB=BM to
     obtain the sorted ``a_quant`` / ``a_scale_sorted_shuffled`` / routing tensors.
  3. Golden: ``aiter.mxfp4_moe_gemm1_a4w4`` with the variant's ``kernelName`` on
     those tensors (for the inline-quant variant gemm1 reads bf16 hidden_states
     directly and quantises inline; both kernels see the same buffers).
  4. FlyDSL: the port (``compile_gemm1_a4w4``) parameterised with the matching
     BM / kUseNT / kInlineQuant on the **same** tensors.
  5. Compare the packed-MXFP4 gemm1 output (``inter_sorted_quant`` packed fp4 +
     ``inter_sorted_shuffled_scale`` e8m0):
       * e8m0 scale bytes must match exactly (integer exponents).
       * packed fp4 nibbles dequantised onto the e2m1 grid compared with
         rtol=1e-3 (the task tolerance).

GPU + aiter (``/tmp/aiter`` on PYTHONPATH) are required; run inside the remote
container (see scripts/REMOTE_DZM.md). The module is collected/skippable when no
GPU / aiter is available.
"""

